s columns map: [0]=year, [1]=month? but values in col1 are small (1 etc.). The 4th col had 2596 which looks like 'DOY?'\n# Actually sample: 2024   1  0 2596 51 52  60  36 ... This is odd. Let's inspect first row parts\nprint(omni_df.iloc[0,:20].tolist())\n\n# Based on OMNI2 low-res format (research): I recall columns: YEAR DOY HOUR? But preview has 2024 1 0 2596 51 52 60 36 ... maybe 2596 is satellite number? Hmm.\n# Simpler approach: find AP-like column by scanning columns for values typically between 0 and 400 with many small integers. We'll compute stats for each column and pick column with median ~5 and max maybe <100.\ncol_stats = []\nfor c in omni_df.columns[:60]:\n    col = pd.to_numeric(omni_df[c], errors='coerce')\n    col_stats.append((c, col.min(skipna=True), col.max(skipna=True), col.median(skipna=True), col.isnull().mean()))\n\n# show candidates where median between 0 and 50 and max <500\ncandidates = [s for s in col_stats if not np.isnan(s[3]) and 0<=s[3]<=50 and s[2]<500]\nsorted(candidates, key=lambda x: (x[3], x[2]))[:30]\n\n", "intent": "Identify TLE-derived semi-major axis time series and locate AP column in OMNI2 file by inspecting column statistics and ranges for candidate AP-like columns."})
